addPriceFeedFor(uint256,uint256,uint256,.details: Existing feeds can't be modified. Neither can feeds that have already been set as defaults (project ID 0).

params.pricingCurrency: The currency the feed's resulting price is in terms of.
params.unitCurrency: The currency being priced by the feed.

params.owner: The address that will own the contract.
params.projects: A contract which mints ERC-721s that represent project ownership and transfers.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

params.decimals: The number of decimals the returned fixed point price should include.
params.pricingCurrency: The currency the feed's resulting price is in terms of.
params.projectId: The ID of the project to check the feed for. Feeds stored in ID 0 are used by default for all projects.
params.unitCurrency: The currency being priced by the feed.

returns._0: The `pricingCurrency` price of 1 `unitCurrency`, as a fixed point number with the specified number of decimals.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

DEFAULT_PROJECT_ID().notice: The ID to store default values in.

PROJECTS().notice: Mints ERC-721s that represent project ownership and transfers.

addPriceFeedFor(uint256,uint256,uint256,.notice: Add a price feed for the `unitCurrency`, priced in terms of the `pricingCurrency`.

pricePerUnitOf(uint256,uint256,uint256,u.notice: Gets the `pricingCurrency` cost for one unit of the `unitCurrency`.

addPriceFeedFor(uint256,uint256,uint256,.details: Existing feeds can't be modified. Neither can feeds that have already been set as defaults (project ID 0).

params.pricingCurrency: The currency the feed's resulting price is in terms of.
params.unitCurrency: The currency being priced by the feed.

params.owner: The address that will own the contract.
params.projects: A contract which mints ERC-721s that represent project ownership and transfers.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

params.decimals: The number of decimals the returned fixed point price should include.
params.pricingCurrency: The currency the feed's resulting price is in terms of.
params.projectId: The ID of the project to check the feed for. Feeds stored in ID 0 are used by default for all projects.
params.unitCurrency: The currency being priced by the feed.

returns._0: The `pricingCurrency` price of 1 `unitCurrency`, as a fixed point number with the specified number of decimals.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

DEFAULT_PROJECT_ID().notice: The ID to store default values in.

PROJECTS().notice: Mints ERC-721s that represent project ownership and transfers.
